5.2 Programme Overview
Blockchain is transforming how organisations manage trust, transparency, digital identity, fundraising, and collaboration. Yet many businesses and social impact organisations struggle to understand where the technology creates genuine value.
This 15-week cohort-based programme is designed to bridge that gap. You'll build a solid foundation in blockchain technology, explore practical use cases across industries, and learn how blockchain products are designed and developed. Whether you're completely new to blockchain or looking to apply it within your organisation, you'll leave with the confidence to evaluate and implement blockchain solutions responsibly.
5.3 Programme Structure
Module
Duration
Description
Module 1 — Blockchain Theory and Fundamentals
5 Weeks
Build a strong understanding of blockchain fundamentals, distributed ledgers, consensus mechanisms, smart contracts, digital assets, wallets, and the core principles that power blockchain networks.
Module 2 — Blockchain in the Real World
5 Weeks
Explore practical blockchain applications across social impact, NGOs, supply chains, finance, governance, identity, fundraising, and enterprise innovation through African and global case studies.
Module 3 — Blockchain Product Development
5 Weeks
Learn how blockchain products are designed, validated, and developed while understanding user needs, product strategy, implementation considerations, and emerging opportunities within the blockchain ecosystem.

